### ðŸ§  What is JVM?

> JVM = Java Virtual Machine
> 
> 
> Runs bytecode (.class) on any OS
> 
> It provides platform independence.
> 

### ðŸ§  What is Bytecode?

> Bytecode = compiled Java code
> 
> 
> Generated by `javac`, executed by JVM
> 
> Platform-independent format
